  "local_port": 55234,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I write answer in engineering exams in English being gujrati medium student?",
  "response": "Writing answers in English for engineering exams can be challenging if you are a Gujarati medium student. However, with the right approach and preparation, you can improve your skills. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you:\n\n1. **Understand the Exam Format**: Familiarize yourself with the exam structure, types of questions, and the marking scheme. This will help you tailor your answers appropriately.\n\n2. **Improve Your English Language Skills**:\n   - **Reading**: Read textbooks, reference materials, and articles related to your engineering subjects in English. This will help you understand technical terminology.\n   - **Writing**: Practice writing daily. Start by summarizing articles or topics in your own words.\n   - **Grammar**: Work on basic grammar rules to construct sentences correctly.\n\n3. **Technical Vocabulary**: Create a glossary of technical terms in both Gujarati and English. Use flashcards or apps to regularly test your vocabulary.\n\n4. **Templates and Structures**:\n   - **Question Understanding**: Start by rewriting the question in your own words to ensure you understand what is being asked.\n   - **Structured Answers**: Use a clear structure for your answers, such as introduction, main body, and conclusion. For problem-solving questions, follow a step-by-step approach.\n   - **Diagrams and Examples**: Where possible, include diagrams or examples to illustrate your points. They can convey understanding even if language skills are lacking.\n\n5. **Practice Past Papers**: Try to practice using past exam papers. This will not only help you get used to the type of questions asked but also improve your speed and confidence.\n\n6. **Seek Feedback**: Work with peers, teachers, or tutors who are proficient in English, and ask for feedback on your written answers.\n\n7. **Use Simple Language**: Focus on clarity and simplicity in your writing. Avoid using complex sentences if you're not comfortable with them.\n\n8. **Time Management**: Practice timing your responses to ensure that you can complete the exam within the given time.\n\n9. **Language Translation Tools**: Use language translation tools sparingly to understand complex materials, but avoid over-reliance. \n\n10. **Join Study Groups**: Participate in study groups where discussions are held in English to enhance your learning and speaking skills.\n\n11. **Online Resources**: Utilize online platforms, like Khan Academy or Coursera, that offer courses in English to improve your academic language skills.\n\nThrough consistent practice and dedication, you will improve in writing exam answers in English. Furthermore, always maintain a positive attitude and believe in your ability to learn and improve.",
